Shroom Gammon Instructions

I am not trying to claim that the original idea for this game was my 
own. I am sure that you will have noticed that the title 'Gammon' has 
given it away.

Back gammon was a game I never wanted to learn. It looked boring 
and it also looked complicated, maybe due to the board having a 
most peculiar look to it! 

One day a friend asked me to play the game but I wasn't really 
interested. But once the rules were sorted out it didn't sound all that 
hard to play. But, it still sounded boring! It looked like there was 
no skill involved and it was all down to the Dice! 

A game based on luck?

Sometimes a bit of luck does come into it but let me tell you, it takes a 
while before you realise how much skill and stratergy IS involved!

Shroom Gammon!!!!! Introduction!

I have always wanted to write my own Back-Gammon game. Many times 
I have gone into my graphics programme and drawn Triangles here 
and Triangles there. Changing the pallete of the screen and using 
some fancy shading here and there but still there was no way of 
getting around the fact that a back-gammon board look's too 
complicated and puts people off from learning how to play.

The hardest thing to get used to is the fact that when you get to 
the end of the board you have to move over to the other side and 
work your way back! You do get used to this after playing the game 
a few times but there does come a time when you make a mistake 
because you miscounted the moves due to the board layout.

I have tried to make it look as simple as possible and also fool people 
into playing Back-Gammon without realising!

Some people have said to me, the game is too simple and cant I add 
a few 'Nasties' or 'teleports!' or something to make it a bit harder. 
But when they play against someone who is used to playing 
Back-gammon they hardly ever win. You see it's not all down to the 
dice!

I am not going to re-write Back-Gammon because its just a perfect 
game! I will however add some extra preferences if you need them.

