Shroom Gammon Game Controls
-----------------------------------

When you are playing the game you have to press on the dice button to
spin them! Then when they have stopped you will know which pieces CAN
move because the pointer will change into two pointers pointing in!

If you want to select this piece you press once then you will be able 
to see where you can move to because the pointer will change to point
down if you can move and if you are pointing over a place you cant move
to the pointer will change into a BLUE CROSS. If you choose to move to
one of your pieces that you can't possible move to then that piece will
then be selected if he can move!

You will get used to it!

If you can't make a legal move then you will be told and you then have a
chance to check if you want to and then click on the small button next to
where it says BLOCKED! this will end your go.

At any time during the game you can choose to see the map. this will 
let you see the whole screen squashed up! Choose map again to exit.

If you don't understand any of the rules then just write to me and I 
will change this document file a little to make it clear. And tell you 
anything you don't understand. 

**************************************************************

You can change the rule settings or go into the game from the main 
screen. Then you can select either a one off match or a league 
game.

The quick match lets you choose names and mushroom colours to be
used. then you will play one game and then it's back to the main menu.

Quick league:-

Same as above but you can have 2-5 players playing each other 1-5 
times. You can see from this that it is possible to play a two player 
best of 5. This is recommended for two player games as it will rule 
out any lucky dice!

As mentioned above there are pts awarded for different win types 1-3 
and this is what goes into the league standings. If two players have 
the same pts at the end of a league then the player who had the 
least doubles will win!

*************************************************************

In the options you can select the type of controls used so if you 
want to use only the mouse then select 'mouse' you will have to 
share the same mouse though. If you want to use a joystick as well 
then select 'Both' else you can select '2 joy' for both players using 
there own joystick. or '1 joy' for both players sharing ' joystick!

